<section class="home-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="home-hero__title">Feedjibacki</h1>
    <p class="home-hero__subtitle">Your personal reviews for products you've bought and tried yourself</p>
    <p class="home-hero__tagline">Rate items, add categories, group them into collections, and leave notes — so when you forget whether you liked something, your own review is waiting for you.</p>

    {{#if viewData.isAuthenticated}}
      <h2 class="home-cta__title">Ready to add or update a review?</h2>
      <a href="/my-items" class="button is-primary">My items</a>
      <a href="/my-collections" class="button is-light">My collections</a>
    {{else}}
      <h2 class="home-cta__title">Create an account and start your personal review log</h2>
      <a href="/signup" class="button is-primary">Sign up</a>
      <span class="home-cta__sep">or</span>
      <a href="/login" class="button is-light">Log in</a>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
</section>

<div class="container">
  <div class="home-features">
    <div class="home-feature">
      <div class="home-feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">📝</div>
      <h2 class="home-feature__title">Remember what you thought</h2>
      <p class="home-feature__text">Keep a private log of items you've purchased and tested. Next time you're at the shop wondering &ldquo;Did I like this?&rdquo;, open the app and read your past self's review.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-feature">
      <div class="home-feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">🏷️</div>
      <h2 class="home-feature__title">Categories &amp; collections</h2>
      <p class="home-feature__text">Tag products with categories and organise them into collections — weekly shop, freezer staples, favourites, or any grouping that matches how you buy.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-feature">
      <div class="home-feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">⭐</div>
      <h2 class="home-feature__title">Ratings &amp; your comments</h2>
      <p class="home-feature__text">Score each item and write notes only you see. Prices, shops, and details can sit alongside the review so you can compare over time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

